values: New Years Resolution: Throw myself down the path towards Enlightenment, and succeed at VCE. That is all.

I'm quitting work.

But that's okay. If I go down, I'm taking the manipulative bitch down with me

Oh, hell yeah. Rough splash, but it almost made me explode with it's awesome.



And yeah, I suck with resizing resoloution and stuff.

So, first up, apologies to everyone for not posting as often as I'd like to. But there are reasons for that!

Moved Huse!

Yeah, so now I live in Pascoe Vale South. Very nice area, though I suppose you could say it's closer to East Brunswick/Moonee Ponds than anything. I am pleased with it, though my room has no real privacy and we still don't have full internet access. Oh well.

Surgery!

I'm still breathing, so  I suppose you could say it went well. No one came to visit, though, so I was lonely in the hopital : ( uh. Recovering still. It really really really hurts, and last night I didn't get to sleep until 6AM when I went and ran myself a warm salt bath which stopped most of the pain and itchiness.
Also, after the hospital I stayed a few days with Dad, which I'm not going to comment on. I spent the whole three days watching DOCTOR WHO and got through the entire Eccleston (spelling?) and Tennant runs. I actually really enjoyed Eccleston - he kind of put me off originally when I realised that despite the looks, he wasn't a chav from Liverpool.. but you know..

So yes. Hurts like a whore but I'm much less sick.

Manifest!

Manifest went swell. Being in a syndicate meant we didn't have to wait in line, and while I didn't get much anime watched I still had a great time. I spent most of it hanging out with my syndicate and the OzTaku crew. Met Lemmy. Filmed a bit. Hung out with Rob. I really can't complain.

Also, Georgia and Anthony are dating. I told you so. I sensed this two years ago.

Writing!

Oh, boy. Well, I came back from hospital only to be told thaf
words_weekly
 had collapsed. Kind of. I still don't have the full story, and while its a shame, I can't help but feel it's my fault. I should've been more dedicated.. and stuff.. well, it probably isn't my fault but you know how it is. I enjoyed the community, and now I know that it'll still running but more loosely.

[Turns out it failed because noone could post on time. Ah, well. Just one of those things.]

Also, I have two unread stories still sitting on my internetless PC. The Science of Laddin Iblis and Martian Gold are the stories, and without giving too much away -

Science is an Arabian-Nights Science-Fiction absurdist comedy in the vein of - maybe - the Discworld tales. It parodies, at a glance, Star Wars and Dune, though it's subtle and stands well on its own. Those who've read it have called me a literary prodigy which makes me feel good. I really enjoy writing comedy.

-----------------------------[Which reminds me, I';m still going to write that story about the Necronomicon being used as a household item and tell it from its own point of view. Just because I don't have to anymore doesn't stop the fact that it's too good an oppurtunity to pass by.]

Martian Gold is a Western set in an alternate 1800's America - my Resiste the Sunne setting, and deals with the explosion of Mars, the advent of extraterrestrial involvement in the southern states, and the rise of a new power source. I wasn't really supposed to have it set in a pre-created world, but it was the only way I'd be able to pull out a western in a week..

I'll upload them when my internet has returned.

I'm also tossing up ideas for an Elseworlds Batman tale. I currently have close to 0, actually. I really suck at fanfiction, so this is hard for me.

And again, I'm plotting my rendition of a vampire tale - inspired by Hellsing, mostly. More on that later.

Anime!

I only just had a chance to finish Trigun, and it made me cry. It was just so sad.. I won't spoil anything, but ohmygod if you havn't seen it .. then.. see it.
I also have to regret finishing Tenjou Tenge. It was unabashadly shounen, which I usually hate, but I fell in love with this series. I havn't been so sad to finish an anime series since Great Teacher Onizuka. And, for a high-school fighting anime, it had great characters and an amazing amount of depth.

Work!

Just on another note, I'm thinking of resigning from work. While I enjoy the job, the fact that I'm being harassed by a certain workmate - hell, it could probably even be considered sexual harrassment, when I think of it - makes it so much more stressful than it has to be. I won't mention any names, since I heard Steph (
zax_dude
) works there now, which may just redeem the place since she's one of the nicest people I've met in a long time.. but still, I don't really have anyone to talk to and while it isn't going to ruin my life it makes me absolutely dread even showing up.

And no, it isn't even the managers. Managers have to be absolute bastards, it's part of their job, so I'll forgive them that.

Let's just leave it at that I'm very happy to be too sore to work. It'll give me a few weeks to sort my shit out. I don't want to quite, because I enjoy the work and the money's so good and I don't want to give up.. but.. *sigh*

Oh well. Enough emo-ness for now. See you.

Why, there have been several reasons, Nathaniel!

1. Writing. For those of you who don't know, I had a challenge for this week.

I needed to write a character-driven story, set in the real world, where the character was transgendered.

It was hard, but I did it. It took me all week, and I lost hair and sleep over it, but now I can say I've written a story where the main character thinks he is a crossdresser. It's brilliant.

2. Work. It would be unproffesional to elaborate, but if I could just flip out and belt some people..

Okay, okay.

So I've been thinking of various table-top/online RPG settings that could be used. This catalogue posts such .. things. This is all mostly fluff, guys, so be warned.

Because my mind works in all fifteen dimensions at once, any one of these could be randomly used as a story idea for teh writing. Setting I, as pitiful as it might sound, has been churning around my head for a long time.

Setting I: Eastwood, City of Ghosts

Stimulus Material: Modern Noir (Sin City-inspired), dark horror, and urban fantasy.
Setting: Eastwood City, found somewhere in North America, has a reputation for it always being dark (due to the odd, gothic architecture of the skyscrapers blocking out the sun) and always raining. It also has a much more sinister reputation; It's known as the most Haunted City in the world, and for good reason. Strange things have been seen in the alleyways, it is rumoured that the Mayor of the city selled his soul to the devil, and gangsters roam the street, manipulating both the mundane and the mystical to keep their crime rings running.
Characters... Will either play as private eyes, femme fatals, criminals, magicians or stranger things. They will not play Werewolves or Vampires. I hate those fucking things.
Anything else? There are currently three unplayable superpowers, vying for dominance over Eastwood, which set the backdrop for the RP:

1. The elusive Circle of E, a cabal of the City's most powerful magicians (who control most of the crime rings AND the politicians in Eastwood, the mayor being a member of the Circle)
2. The Quansithilium Corporation Group, which specializes in developing and testing psychic/magickal/alienish technology and weapons - being supported by several of the worlds richest men, as well as at least two prominent mercenary group - made them stand at a sort of cold-war between Quansithilium and the Circle.
3. Finally, the newcomers to Eastwood - the mysterious Drachenorden, or Order of the Dragon, whose task is to protect their liege, Sigismund, widely considered to be one of the most powerful magicians in the world. The Drachenorden consists of exactly 13 members, each of them incredibly skilled and dangerous. The Drachenorden broke the fragile balance of power that had been present in Eastwood.

What do you think? Could it possibly work?
